nded concept representations that include newly inferred attributes or roles. The entire pipeline is trained end-to-end using a multi-task objective: reconstruction accuracy of masked KG triples, preservation of hierarchical entailment (inspired by NLI tasks in Paper 3), and coherence of expanded concepts in downstream applications like question answering or abstractive summarization. This approach enables models to go beyond static embeddings—concepts become dynamic, composable, and contextually aware, yet structurally anchored. Potential impact includes improved performance in reasoning-intensive NLP tasks, better interpretability of concept evolution, and scalable integration of symbolic knowledge into deep learning systems.",
